title: Ryan Sweeting wants Kaley Cuoco to give him spousal support
text:
Ryan Sweeting wants Kaley Cuoco to give him spousal support Compiled by Tony Hicks Posted: 10/20/2015 09:23:13 AM PDT Updated: 10/20/2015 09:33:14 AM PDT Ryan Sweeting wants spousal support from Kaley Cuoco, according to Entertainment Tonight, which apparently got its mitts on their divorce papers. 
According to CBS, "The Big Bang Theory" actress is worth about $45 million, compared to the pro tennis player's $2 million. 
Sounds like someone needs to get out and practice more. 
Cuoco filed for divorce last month, after 20 months of marriage. They had a prenuptial agreement. 
The 29-year-olds married on New Year's Eve 2013 and have no children. 
Cuoco's publicist has said the split was mutual and "they ask for privacy at this time. No further statement will be issued regarding this matter." In this Dec. 18, 2014 file photo, Ryan Sweeting, and Kaley Cuoco arrive at the People Magazine Awards at the Beverly Hilton in Beverly Hills, Calif. (Photo by Chris Pizzello/Invision/AP, File) Tony Hicks writes celebrity commentary for the Bay Area News Group.
